Binance is the leading global blockchain ecosystem and cryptocurrency
infrastructure provider whose suite of financial products includes the world’s
largest digital-asset exchange.

Our mission is to accelerate cryptocurrency adoption and increase the freedom
of money.

If you’re looking for a fast-paced, mission-driven organization where
opportunities to learn and excel are endless, then Binance is the place for
you.

We are looking for a Senior DevOps or DevOps Architect to help us push our
infrastructure and configuration management to the next level.

You'll have experience in designing, implementing, and maintaining large-
scale, complex, highly critical applications.

Your tasks will involve designing, implementing and improving our next-
generation infrastructure management. Advancing our infrastructure and
architecture, you'll help migrate existing systems while working closely with
the Dev and QA teams. They'll find technical solutions to prevent or mitigate
production issues, and automate devOps and operations tasks.

  * Develop, maintain and administer tools which will automate operational activities and improve engineering productivity 
  * Proposing and driving architecture improvements, recommending process improvements 
  * Find solutions to production issues after root cause analysis 
  * Automate continuous delivery and on-demand capacity management solutions 
  * Developing configuration and infrastructure solutions for internal deployments 
  * Updating, tracking and resolving technical issues 
  * Evaluate new technology options and vendor products. Ensuring critical system security through the use of best in class security solutions 

  * 7+ years of technical experience in a similar role architecting and supporting large scale production systems 
  * Experienced with cloud services such as AWS and GCP 
  * Experience in large-scaled distributed environments 
  * Demonstrated robust programming skill in Python, Go, or similar 
  * Experience with tools such as Saltstack, Terraform, Ansible, Docker, etc 
  * Proficiency with Linux 
  * Bachelor's degree in a technical field 

